signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Shutdown defenders have the talent to erase receivers from the game. When they enter the zone, their coverage is tighter and interceptions are more frequent on contested catches.
Defenders with this ability generally react much faster to receiver cut moves when in man coverage and outside the numbers
Players with this ability are more likely to succeed at and attempt diving catches and swats.
Defenders with this ability force more catch tackle knockouts in man-to-man versus short routes less than 10 yards from LoS
Aggressive receivers overpower defenders and attack the football. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their success rate on aggressive catches against single coverage.
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes 10-20 yards from the LoS, inside the numbers
Receivers with this ability make sharper cuts and frequently win contested catches when covered by linebackers and linemen.
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes less than 10 yards from the LoS, inside the numbers
The game's top defenders excel in all situations. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their chance of defeating run blocks, and disrupting catches via tackles.
Defenders with this ability have an increased success rate when using conservative or diving tackles.
Defenders with this ability force more catch knockouts and react quicker in any flat zone coverage, less than 10 yards from the LoS and outside the hash marks.
Defenders with this ability force more catch knockouts and react quicker in any mid-field zone coverage, less than 20 yards from the LoS inside the numbers and 10-20 outside.
Freight Trains are relentless runners who refuse to go down on first contact. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their chance to break the next tackle.
Ballcarriers with this ability have more powerful stiff arm animations and have a larger timing window for landing perfect stiff arms.
Ballcarriers with this ability have an increased chance to break hit-stick tackle attempts made on them.
Ballcarriers with this ability will cause increased fatigue penalties against their tackler when tackled via a non-conservative tackle.
The most effective ball carriers prioritize maintaining possession over all else. When they enter the zone, no tackles made against them will result in a fumble.
Passers with this ability receive better blocking support on designed quarterback run plays.
Passers with this ability have faster passing animations when they are throwing under pressure
Ballcarriers with this ability have steerable juke animations.
Passers with this ability improve the catching prowess of all tight ends who are open on pass plays.
While in the pocket, passers with this ability are almost guaranteed to evade the first sack attempt by a blitzing defensive back.
The game's top defenders excel in all situations. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their chance of defeating run blocks, and disrupting catches via tackles.
Defenders with this ability have better conservative/dive tackling, are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves, and cannot be faked out when user-controlled.
Defenders with this ability force more catch knockouts and react quicker in any mid-field zone coverage, less than 20 yards from the LoS inside the numbers and 10-20 outside.
Defenders with this ability will cause increased fatigue penalties when tackling a ballcarrier with a non-conservative tackle.
Blockers with this ability reduce a rusher's chances of using a quick block shed move.
Blockers with this ability reduce an edge pass rusher's chances of using a quick block shed move
Blockers with this ability reduce a rusher's chances of using a quick block shed move while run blocking.
Zone Hawk defenders lock down a part of the field. When they enter the zone, this ability increases the rate of interceptions while in zone coverage.
